headline: Nasdaq, Inc. Announces Cash Tender Offers for Up to $200 Million Outstanding Debt Securities
summary: NEW YORK, Feb. 10, 2025 (GLOBE NEWSWIRE) -- Nasdaq, Inc. (Nasdaq: NDAQ) (“Nasdaq” or the “Company”) today announced its offers to purchase for cash up to an aggregate principal amount of $200,000,000 (the “Aggregate Notes Cap”) of its outstanding Notes, comprised of (i) up to $40,000,000 aggregate principal amount (the “2028 Notes Cap”) of the Company’s 5.350% Senior Notes due 2028 (the “2028 Notes”), (ii) up to $50,000,000 aggregate principal amount (the “2034 Notes Cap”) of the Company’s 5.550
